@startuml failsafe_mode_to_edr_storage_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Failsafe Mode To EDR Storage Signal Flow\n(Core fail-safe / alert severity -> EDR storage escalation)

participant "CGW / CoreState\nfail-safe context" as CoreCtx #F4F7FB
participant "EDR\nevent data recorder" as EDR #E8F7E8
participant "EDR storage /\nevidence bus" as StorageBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / diagnostics" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Fail-safe Inputs ==

CoreCtx -> EDR : Core::failSafeMode\nwarningPathStatus\ne2eHealthState\nselectedAlertLevel
EDR -> EDR : eventSeverity =\n3 if alert >= 4\n2 if alert >= 3 or failSafe > 0\n1 if alert > 0
EDR -> EDR : storageState = high if failSafe == 2 or severity >= 3
EDR -> EDR : storageLevel = severity*20 + warningPath*10 + degraded E2E bonus
note right of EDR
Representative escalation inputs
- failSafeMode
- warningPathStatus
- e2eHealthState
- selectedAlertLevel
end note

== Storage Publication ==

EDR -> StorageBus : frmEdrStateMsg\nStorageState / StorageLevel / EventSeverity
EDR -> Obs : diagnostic event trace /\nEDR readback
note right of EDR
Representative outputs
- EventSeverity
- StorageState
- StorageLevel
end note

note over CoreCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Core fail-safe and alert context reach EDR
2. EDR escalates severity and storage policy
3. Recorder publishes storage state for diagnostics/evidence
4. Observers expose the preserved fail-safe event level
end note

@enduml
